Usage:

    python hdr.py <num_frame> <ref_frame> <MTB_level> <radius> <sigma_s> <sigma_r> <contrast> <path_to_data>


ref_frame:
    reference picture in alignment
MTB_level:
    level in MTB algorithm
radius:

sigma_s:

sigma_r:

contrast:

path_to_data:
    the path to image data.


All the input images must has file extension 'jpg', case sensitive. (.JPG is invalid)
Only input imgaes can be inside <path_to_data>, no other files can exist.

Result of two versions of tone mapping algorithm is named 'result_photo.jpg', 'result_bilateral.jpg'
HDR output image is named 'result_hdr.hdr'
